i am fearful that the euthanasia didn't work is it possible i'm scared my cat wasn't 'put to sleep' properly because when she was passed to me wrapped in a blanket she was still warm the vet did check for a heartbeat afterwards he said there wasn't one i even looked at her and pressed my hand against her stomach chest and she wasn't breathing she has since been buried and i'm so scared i buried her when she was still alive i'm just so scared her heart could have restarted is this just an irrational thought because i am grieving purrs and prayers to you for your loss a cat's normal body temperature is a little higher than ours averaging about degrees so she would feel 'warm' to you the drug used for euthanasia is very effective and causes a quick and gentle death the concerns you are having for burying her prematurely are part of your grief over her death you are going thru the natural and normal grief process the steps are shock denial anger bargaining depression and acceptance please go to petloss com they have excellent pet grief help Grief First aid Cat EastEnders Anxiety Characters in the Smurfs Cardiac arrhythmia Drowning Milton H. Erickson Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Death Stillbirth Cardiopulmonary resuscitation Shaggy dog story Vampire Thermoregulation Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Paracetamol Sin City Sleep Clinical depression Pitaten Avalanche Hypothermia Childbirth Anorexia nervosa Hypnosis Funeral Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Knots Landing Stroke Dead Like Me Miscarriage Suicide methods Days of our Lives Burial Cancer Panic attack Equine conformation Bipolar disorder Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Shock Kurt Cobain Mummy Jewish bereavement Breech birth W.I.T.C.H. Night (book) The Subtle Knife Peter Singer Sharia Tlingit Characters of Naruto StarCraft: Uprising Dog Tobacco smoking Euphemism Care Bears Cryonics Poker jargon YuYu Hakusho The League of Gentlemen (comedy) 3-quinuclidinyl benzilate Wolfrider Anger management Lethal injection Prostate cancer 24 Hours